<subSubSection id="C5FD0590E2CFBBF05C90FE283B5F03E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="101C6D2D28377C241DEC50BC9CFB55A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="956030B2809A0BDA0EF16B3313E6C708" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">The epithet refers to the flabellate shape of emergences on leaves.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A454F6EED2D4EBBE03FCA195ABBF0160" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0B16DEA3C81EB38187F55F844FDECD0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="17C47CE75148233DE40B676E23DA79E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Only one population was found on rocks in a stream in Manandriana, Madagascar (
<geoCoordinate id="49037D7967EEAF654F16E85AEAEF29E9" degrees="20" direction="south" minutes="14" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-20.233334">20°14'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
