<subSubSection id="19DBD43D95FB00180CCB22022CC55B72" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="516715341F00B5A39FA78FACD2657ED5" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6818B7872DD9F12BDFECCB0F45657914" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="853DE52B274858EC9A414F8F68B94432" authorityName="G. W. Hu, Zhun Xu &amp; Q. F. Wang" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrostachyaceae" genus="Hydrostachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hydrostachys flabellifera" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flabellifera">
<emphasis id="D73E95A2C41CD60BAC2466164DFF81E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Hydrostachys flabellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently only known from one location with a very small population. Additionally, all species of 
<taxonomicName id="6343550C01EF2D11EFAE4BF7AC298CAB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrostachyaceae" genus="Hydrostachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hydrostachys" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1EFC539BFA0A764A398217A26511FF25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Hydrostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are highly dependent on the moving aquatic environment which is threatened by water pollution, natural system modifications, energy production and mining, all of which could drive the taxon to Critically Endangered (CR) or Extinct (EX) in a very short time (
<bibRefCitation id="FD8DA714CEC4339E04E95F1F668D46FD" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org" refId="B10" refString="IUCN, 2020. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2020-2. http://www.iucnredlist.org" title="The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. Version 2020 - 2." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org" year="2020">IUCN 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Following Guidelines for IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (2020), 
<taxonomicName id="7CE2CF44A1E68E423B38C5F9E2157821" genus="H." lsidName="H. flabellifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="flabellifera">
<emphasis id="65C44BB3A02118DC1878F0551182218C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. flabellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be categorised as Vulnerable (VU D2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D3394C83267CE2BB53D1FA9F5C84A3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="phylogenetic analysis">
<paragraph id="C91374343157077D85533F2C156D9E7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Phylogenetic analysis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A80414C4005D7791D59FF413ED9B32A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<taxonomicName id="C9A7B9D9955713A45F0407A43F3FB119" authorityName="G. W. Hu, Zhun Xu &amp; Q. F. Wang" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrostachyaceae" genus="Hydrostachys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hydrostachys flabellifera" order="Cornales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flabellifera">
<emphasis id="D6F0289FF5739E7137A5E91AE77B5158" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Hydrostachys flabellifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in a robust clade together with 
<taxonomicName id="D5E4B5682A9BC2E40C4C4C610C82D4FF" genus="H." lsidName="H. stolonifera" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="stolonifera">
<emphasis id="03DEC78C43FB0099494E453075F25E2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. stolonifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C3C445DECAC581ED0C25CC8C08C77D32" genus="H." lsidName="H. imbricata" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="imbricata">
<emphasis id="206335359A6FE988052E83B632854AB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. imbricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2F6A40966A3F374299EE5B6E1220143" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Maximum Likelihood tree, based on ITS. Bootstrap values are labelled alongside each node." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.167.58538.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/477540" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4</figureCitation>
) with a high bootstrap support (BS = 96%), while they share limited morphological characteristics. 
<taxonomicName id="A17239534865718D7B93954DDE317912" genus="H." lsidName="H. multifida" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" rank="species" species="multifida">
<emphasis id="09DC1AE7240A3456247B02E8BC34CBA1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">H. multifida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, considered as a clade in morphology, is not a monophyletic group, although with low bootstrap support.
</paragraph>
